'Josie from Glasgow.Stayed from 20th to 23rd May.First visit to Aberdeen.Doing a bit of family history and meeting relatives.Guest house in great area quiet, although near city centre ,train and bus stations.Rooms price good,clean,comfy bed,and great view from my window.Breakfast great even got my gluten free bread and sausages.as I am coeliac.Staff Isobel and Cathy very nice.Had a great weekend and would go back if in Aberdeen again. Room Tip: I had single ensuite room on top floor See more room tips'